sql:
SELECT AVG(tx_price) AS average_transaction_price
FROM properties
WHERE beds = 3 AND baths = 2;

external_knowledge:
- 'Decent number of rooms' refers to properties with 3 to 5 bedrooms;
- 'Upscale' implies good to excellent property conditions;
- 'Average price of homes' corresponds to the average transaction price of the properties.

sql:
SELECT AVG(tx_price) AS average_transaction_price
FROM properties
WHERE last_sold_date >= DATE('now', '-1 year');

SELECT COUNT(sale_id) AS number_of_sales
FROM property_sales
WHERE strftime('%Y', sale_date) = '2023';

SELECT AVG(tx_price) AS average_transaction_price
FROM properties
WHERE neighborhood_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "peaks of property wealth" refers to neighborhoods with high median home values;
- "golden houses" symbolizes properties in those neighborhoods;
- "mountain tops of median home values" metaphorically refers to the highest median home values in the neighborhoods;
- "shine of their school district stars" represents the ratings of the school districts in those neighborhoods.

